race.comment: RUN RORY RUN (2) travelled in the leading division then dug deep to hold onto third last start over 1500m at Newcastle. Races well at Taree and from a good gate will enjoy the run of the race around his favourite circuit. Represents excellent value in early markets. SPIRITLY (11) scored here at this trip two back then caught the eye late over 1800m at Port Macquarie last Saturday. In fine form and this scenario sets up ideally. SCOTLAND (5) cantered in two back in open company at Bowraville before getting too far back at Newcastle last time. Good chance if ridden with a bit of aggression. ANCIENT EGYPT (3) dominated at Gunnedah recently. Major candidate with a repeat of that effort. Pre-post favourite AUZSTAR (1) was impressive at Port Macquarie last time but 63kgs is a decent steadier.
